{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "targeted_sweep6_pool_ideology_full",
    "description": "Full-network validation of targeted_sweep2b pool ideology findings.\ntargeted_sweep2b ran on the lite network with the role-name bug \u2014 economic and user node parameters were never applied, so the actual economic context was the baked-in YAML default (~43% v27 custody) rather than the intended 0.78. The pool ideology and max_loss parameters were correctly applied, so the diagonal threshold finding (ideology \u00d7 max_loss \u2273 0.12) is directionally plausible but unverified.\nThis sweep is an exact replica of targeted_sweep2b's grid and fixed parameters on the full 60-node network with the fixed build script. Results will directly answer:\n  1. Does the diagonal threshold (ideology \u00d7 max_loss \u2273 0.12) hold on the\n     full network, or was it an artifact of the lite network's wrong economic\n     conditions?\n  2. Is the executive summary's pool ideology finding trustworthy?\n\nExpected outcome if finding holds:\n                     pool_max_loss_pct\nideology_strength   0.05  0.15  0.25  0.35  0.45\n       0.2           26    26    26    26    26\n       0.4           26    26    26    27    27\n       0.6           26    26    27    27    27\n       0.8           26    27    27    27    27\n\nAny deviation from this pattern reveals a network-size effect on pool ideology dynamics that was previously invisible.\n",
    "spec_file": "specs/targeted_sweep6_pool_ideology_full.yaml",
    "base_network": "full",
    "n_samples": 20,
    "n_parameters": 16,
    "grid_axes": {
